FT  01 JUL 94 / UK Company News: Booth Inds losses rise to Pounds 2.12m
Difficulties in its structural steel division left Booth Industries, the
specialist engineer, with increased pre-tax losses of Pounds 2.12m for the
year to March 31, against Pounds 576,000.
The activities of the division have been curtailed resulting in a provision
of Pounds 1.43m.
Losses per share came out at 52.52p (11.53p) and the dividend is passed.
Last year only an interim of 0.7p was paid. Turnover was Pounds 16.5m
(Pounds 18.9m).
